NAME
    git-gone - Purge a file from your Git history

SYNOPSIS
    git-gone filename.extension

DESCRIPTION
    git-gone removes a file from the Git history of a Git repository. The script must be run in the root directory of the Git repository.

OPTIONS
    filename.extension
        The path and/or filename of the file to be removed from the Git history.

RETURN VALUE
    The script returns 0 on success, and a non-zero value on failure.

ERRORS
    If the current directory is not a Git repository, the script reports an error message and exits with a non-zero status code.
    If the specified file does not exist in the Git history, the script reports an error message and exits with a non-zero status code.
    If any of the Git operations fail, the script reports an error message and exits with a non-zero status code.

